abstract: At least 304 people have been killed in Iran during anti-government unrest that broke out last month, Amnesty International said on Tuesday.
snippet: At least 304 people have been killed in Iran during anti-government unrest that broke out last month, Amnesty International said on Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: DUBAI — At least 304 people have been killed in Iran during anti-government unrest that broke out last month, Amnesty International said on Tuesday.
headline_main: Amnesty Says 304 Killed in Iran Unrest, Thousands Arrested Including Children
headline_print_headline: Amnesty Says 304 Killed in Iran Unrest, Thousands Arrested Including Children

abstract: U.S. Democratic presidential candidate Pete Buttigieg pledged on Monday to end the Trump administration's "discriminatory policies" toward Latinos, as the South Bend, Indiana, mayor looks for ways to boost his appeal among minority voters.
snippet: U.S. Democratic presidential candidate Pete Buttigieg pledged on Monday to end the Trump administration's "discriminatory policies" toward Latinos, as the South Bend, Indiana, mayor looks for ways to boost his appeal among minority voters.
lead_paragraph: DETROIT — U.S. Democratic presidential candidate Pete Buttigieg pledged on Monday to end the Trump administration's "discriminatory policies" toward Latinos, as the South Bend, Indiana, mayor looks for ways to boost his appeal among minority voters.
headline_main: Buttigieg Pledges 'New Era' for U.S. Latinos in Push for Minority Voters
headline_print_headline: Buttigieg Pledges 'New Era' for U.S. Latinos in Push for Minority Voters

abstract: The Supreme Court will not review an appellate decision that makes it harder for cities to keep homeless people from sleeping on the streets.
snippet: The Supreme Court will not review an appellate decision that makes it harder for cities to keep homeless people from sleeping on the streets.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Supreme Court will not review an appellate decision that makes it harder for cities to keep homeless people from sleeping on the streets.
headline_main: Supreme Court Won't Revive Homeless Camping Ban in Idaho
headline_print_headline: Supreme Court Won't Revive Homeless Camping Ban in Idaho

abstract: Irish nationalists and pro-British unionists in Northern Ireland began talks on Monday to restore devolved government to the province at a time when the United Kingdom's imminent departure from the European Union threatens the already delicate political balance.
snippet: Irish nationalists and pro-British unionists in Northern Ireland began talks on Monday to restore devolved government to the province at a time when the United Kingdom's imminent departure from the European Union threatens the already delicate pol...
lead_paragraph: BELFAST — Irish nationalists and pro-British unionists in Northern Ireland began talks on Monday to restore devolved government to the province at a time when the United Kingdom's imminent departure from the European Union threatens the already delicate political balance.
headline_main: To Brexit Backdrop, Northern Ireland Parties Try to Restore Devolved Government
headline_print_headline: To Brexit Backdrop, Northern Ireland Parties Try to Restore Devolved Government

abstract: The New Jersey Democrat has quickly become anathema to people on both sides of the political divide after news spread he planned to switch parties.
snippet: The New Jersey Democrat has quickly become anathema to people on both sides of the political divide after news spread he planned to switch parties.
lead_paragraph: TRENTON, N.J. — When Representative Jeff Van Drew, a moderate Democrat who has staunchly opposed impeaching President Trump, decided to jump to the Republican Party, he got Mr. Trump’s encouragement and blessing.

abstract: The European Commission urged Malta on Monday to speed up reforms to ensure the independence of its judiciary amid uproar over the investigation into the 2017 murder of journalist Daphne Caruana Galizia.
snippet: The European Commission urged Malta on Monday to speed up reforms to ensure the independence of its judiciary amid uproar over the investigation into the 2017 murder of journalist Daphne Caruana Galizia.
lead_paragraph: BRUSSELS — The European Commission urged Malta on Monday to speed up reforms to ensure the independence of its judiciary amid uproar over the investigation into the 2017 murder of journalist Daphne Caruana Galizia.
headline_main: EU Tells Malta to Hasten Push for Independent Judges, Prosecutors
headline_print_headline: EU Tells Malta to Hasten Push for Independent Judges, Prosecutors

abstract: From profiles of Arthur Jafa and Jasper Johns to an exploration of how, and why, artists trade work, some of our favorite pieces from 2019.
snippet: From profiles of Arthur Jafa and Jasper Johns to an exploration of how, and why, artists trade work, some of our favorite pieces from 2019.
lead_paragraph: This year, we visited the famously reclusive Jasper Johns at his barn in the Berkshire Mountains, caught up with Nick Cave and his fanciful Soundsuits on Chicago’s Northwest Side, looked at how and why artists exchange their work and tried to figure out the most important pieces of art made in the last 50 years. Below, a roundup of our favorite art stories of 2019.

abstract: Police detained dozens of people in Kazakhstan's two main cities on Monday at rare protests demanding political reform and the sidelining of the family of former President Nursultan Nazarbayev.
snippet: Police detained dozens of people in Kazakhstan's two main cities on Monday at rare protests demanding political reform and the sidelining of the family of former President Nursultan Nazarbayev.
lead_paragraph: ALMATY/NUR-SULTAN — Police detained dozens of people in Kazakhstan's two main cities on Monday at rare protests demanding political reform and the sidelining of the family of former President Nursultan Nazarbayev.
headline_main: Dozens Detained in Rare Kazakhstan Independence Day Protests
